<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li><p>
</p><p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Fix Image.</p><img alt="Number line." role="image" src="../../../../../../figures/tikz-file-149743.svg"/><p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Fix Image.</p><img alt="Expand image" src="../../../../../assets/expand-9ef5655e2d1b5ba286de1390c97f4243f15e264c89106027f5d071073ab562bb.png" title="Expand image"/><p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Fix Image.</p><img alt="Number line." role="image" src="../../../../../../figures/tikz-file-149743.svg" width="80%"/><p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Fix Image.</p><img alt="Number line." role="image" src="../../../../../../figures/tikz-file-149744.svg"/><p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Fix Image.</p><img alt="Expand image" src="../../../../../assets/expand-9ef5655e2d1b5ba286de1390c97f4243f15e264c89106027f5d071073ab562bb.png" title="Expand image"/><p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Fix Image.</p><img alt="Number line." role="image" src="../../../../../../figures/tikz-file-149744.svg" width="80%"/>
      </li>
      <li><p>Sample responses:</p><ul>
<li><m>\frac{1}{2} = \frac{4}{8}</m></li>
<li><m>\frac{1}{3} = \frac{2}{6}</m></li>
<li><m>\frac{6}{8} = \frac{3}{4}</m></li>
<li><m>\frac{2}{3} = \frac{4}{6}</m></li>
</ul>
      </li>
    </ol>
<p>If you have time: Sample response: <m>\frac{3}{2}</m> is equivalent to <m>\frac{6}{4}</m> because they are at the same point on the number line. </p>
